Egypt Constitutional Committee Close to Ending Work, MENA Says

-- B y   M a h m o u d   K a s s e m
-- 
2011-02-19T15:09:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/egypt-constitutional-committee-close-to-ending-work-mena-says.html
  Egypt ’s constitutional committee is
close to finishing the tasks it was set, including amending laws
that concern presidential elections and their oversight, the
state-run Middle East News Agency reported today, citing the
head of the committee, Tarek El Bishry.  The committee, formed by the army, will complete its work
“within days,” the news service reported. A report on the
progress of the committee will be presented tomorrow, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mahmoud Kassem in Cairo at 
 mkassem1@bloomberg.net   To contact the reporter on this story:
Riad Hamade at   rhamade@bloomberg.net  